+ java.lang.Object
+ java.lang.Thread

+ public class 
	+extends Thread
	+implements Runnable
	
+ A thread is a thread of execution in a program. 
+ The Java Virtual Machine allows an application to have multiple threads of execution running concurrently.

States/ LifeCycle of Thread
	New
	Runnable
	Blocked
	Waiting
	Timed Waiting
	Terminated
	
+ Thread with run method, main is already a thread
+ thread object with start() - initiates the other thread
Running tasks from Thread and Runnable
Strategies for returning values from Threads and Runnable tasks
wait(), notify(), join(), sleep()
 	